structured.description: A `Camera` class that handles view and projection matrices for a 3D camera. The class has an abstract `calculateProjectionMatrix` method that returns a matrix for a specific camera type, and an `adjustToViewport` method that resizes the camera based on its dimensions. The class also contains a `getTranslationMatrix` method that returns a matrix representing the camera's position in 3D space. Finally, the code defines a `CameraStruct` class that serves as a base class for other camera types and provides an abstract `getAsMatrix4` method for returning the camera's transformation matrix in a standard format.

items.description: Is an abstract class with various methods and fields used for camera manipulation. The class has a Matrix4f representation of the camera's projection and view projection matrices, as well as a Transform structure for storing camera position and rotation information. Additionally, there are methods for calculating the view matrix and translation matrix, and an abstract method for calculating the projection matrix based on a CameraStruct data object.
items.name: Camera

items.description: Computes and returns a matrix representing the view projection transformation, based on the current view matrix and any changes to the transform property.

returns.description: a `Matrix4f` object representing the view projection matrix.

items.name: getViewProjection

items.description: Computes the view matrix for a given camera transformation, including rotation and translation.

returns.description: a 4x4 matrix representing the view transformation of a camera.

usage.description:
In this example, MyCamera is a subclass of Camera and overrides two methods from its superclass: calculateProjectionMatrix() and adjustToViewport(). The calculateProjectionMatrix() method returns a Matrix4f representing the projection matrix for the camera, while the adjustToViewport() method adjusts the position of the camera to fit within a viewport of width and height.

Inside MyCamera's constructor, the superclass's constructor is called with an instance of Matrix4f as an argument, which represents the projection matrix. This instance will be used by the calculateProjectionMatrix() method to return the projection matrix for the camera.

When using this class, the programmer can create a MyCamera object and pass an instance of Matrix4f representing the desired projection matrix to its constructor. The created object can then use the calculateProjectionMatrix() method to get the projection matrix for the camera.

The programmer can also use the adjustToViewport() method to adjust the position of the camera to fit within a viewport of width and height.

items.name: calculateViewMatrix

items.description: Generates a 4x4 matrix representing a translation from the origin, based on a vector of coordinates representing the displacement.

returns.description: a 4x4 matrix representing the translation of the camera position from its previous location.

items.name: getTranslationMatrix

items.description: Retrieves the value of the `transform` instance variable and returns it.

returns.description: a reference to an instance of the `Transform` class.

items.name: getTransform

items.description: Is an abstract class that acts as a base for other classes in the "Camera" package. It contains an abstract method called getAsMatrix4() and does not have any fields or methods of its own. The purpose of this class is to provide a common interface for subclasses of Camera to implement.
items.name: CameraStruct

structured.description: A `Model` class that loads and renders 3D models using OpenGL. The class takes in an array of vertices and an array of indices to render the model. It also defines several methods for binding and unbinding vertex arrays, enabling and disabling vertex attributes, and getting the VAO handle and size of the model.

items.description: Is used for rendering 3D models in a graphics application. It takes care of binding vertex arrays and storing data and indices for rendering. The class provides methods to enable and disable vertex attribs, get the VAO ID and size, and load data from an array and indices for rendering.
items.name: Model

items.description: Binds a vertex array object, enables vertex attributes, draws a collection of triangles using `glDrawElements`, and disables the vertex attributes again.
items.name: draw

items.description: Enables two vertex attributes in a 3D graphics context using OpenGL API.
items.name: enableAttribs

items.description: Disables vertex attribute arrays for both attributes, GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_BUFFER and GL_NORMAL_ARRAY_BUFFER, using `glDisableVertexAttribArray`.
items.name: disableAttribs

items.description: Returns the value of the variable `vao`.

returns.description: the value of the `vao` field, which is an integer.

usage.code:
Model model = Model.load(vertices, indices); // load the model from vertices and indices array
int vao = model.getVAO();  // get VAO from loaded model
GL30.glBindVertexArray(vao);  // bind VAO to draw

items.name: getVAO

items.description: Returns the current size of an object's storage.

usage.code:
Model model = Model.load(vertices, indices);
int size = model.getSize();

items.name: getSize

items.description: Loads a 3D model into memory by creating a Vertex Array Object (VAO), storing index data, and then binding the VAO to the GPU for rendering.

params.name: vertices
params.description: 3D model's geometry as a set of floating-point coordinates, which are stored in an array and passed to the `storeData()` method for storage in the Vertex Array Object (VAO).

params.name: indices
params.description: 3D model's vertex array object (VAO) indices, which are used to bind the model's vertices and indices to the appropriate buffers for rendering.

returns.description: a `Model` object representing the loaded 3D model.

items.name: load

items.description: Creates a new vertex array object (VAO) and binds it to the current GL context, allowing for efficient rendering of 3D models.

returns.description: an integer value representing a valid vertex array object (VAO) handle.

items.name: createVAO

items.description: Generates a vertex buffer object (VBO), binds it, and stores data in it using the `GL15.glBufferData()` method. It then sets up vertex attributers for the data.

params.name: attrib
params.description: 2D vertex attribute index that contains the data to be stored in the VBO.

params.name: data
params.description: 3D data to be stored in the vertex buffer object (VBO).

items.name: storeData

items.description: Generates a new buffer for storing indices, binds it, and stores the input array of indices in it using the `GL15.glBufferData()` method.

params.name: indices
params.description: 3D model's indices that are to be stored in the element array buffer.

items.name: storeIndices

items.description: Disables the Vertex Array Object (VAO) bound to it by passing a value of 0 to the `glBindVertexArray` method.
items.name: unbindVAO
